schms-selection-and-snapshot-parity — deterministic enumeration for portable drawing snapshots
================================================================================================

Context
-------

SCHMS regression tests need to snapshot all relevant entities, or a filtered
subset, after a batch operation.  The snapshot normalizer belongs to SCHMS,
but clautolisp must expose the same observable entity set and filtering
semantics as AutoCAD and BricsCAD.

This issue is a focused dependency of the SCHMS regression corpus and is
related to, but smaller than, `drawing-database-api.issue`.

Required subset
---------------

Audit and complete:

  - `(ssget "X" ...)` over the active in-memory drawing;
  - filters used by SCHMS, initially entity type (0), layer (8), handle (5),
    block name (2), layout/model space indicators and XData/regapp filters;
  - SSLENGTH, SSNAME, SSADD, SSDEL and membership/duplicate behaviour needed by
    the test helpers;
  - traversal with ENTNEXT/ENTLAST when selection sets do not expose a required
    non-graphical object;
  - deterministic tests that distinguish semantic set equality from accidental
    iteration order.

The runtime need not promise the same raw enumeration order across engines.
It must provide the same membership and data, allowing the SCHMS normalizer to
sort by semantic keys.

Vendor probes
-------------

Create portable probes for filter conjunction, absent groups, erased entities,
subentities, paperspace/modelspace, XData filters and malformed filter lists.
Record dialect differences explicitly.

Acceptance
----------

  - The initial SCHMS snapshot helper obtains the same logical entity
    membership under AutoCAD, BricsCAD and clautolisp.
  - Supported filters have portable conformance tests and documented error
    behaviour.
  - Erased entities and subentities are included or excluded consistently with
    the selected CAD profile.
  - Tests do not rely on mock-host insertion order unless vendor behaviour
    makes that order contractual.
  - Existing suites remain green on SBCL and CCL.

Out of scope
------------

Interactive selection (`ssget` point/window prompts), graphical hit testing,
viewport rendering and pixel comparisons.


SCHMS call inventory (recorded 2026-07-24)
------------------------------------------
The SCHMS+ AutoLISP call inventory is committed at
issues/open/schms-call-inventory.md (acceptance item #1). It calibrates
ordering/priority; per pjb the implementation targets the FULL AutoLISP
spec + AutoCAD/BricsCAD reference, not only the SCHMS subset.


STATUS (2026-07-24, branch schms-data-selection, clautolisp 1.6.8+)
===================================================================
Headless core: DONE.   Vendor verification: BLOCKED on live CAD access.

Implemented (headless, green now)
---------------------------------
- (ssget "X" filter) / (ssget "_X" filter): whole-database scan over the
  active in-memory drawing, returning GRAPHICAL entities only
  (dictionaries/xrecords excluded, matching the vendor).
- FULL ssget filter grammar (selection-api.lisp, parsed to a predicate
  tree once, evaluated per entity):
    * attribute tests on any group code (0 type, 2 block name, 5 handle,
      8 layer, 62 colour, ...);
    * string values: WCMATCH wildcard grammar + comma-alternation (so an
      8-code comma-joined layer list matches any listed layer);
    * -3 XData application filter: per-application sublists, wildcard
      application names, optional inner (code . value) constraints;
    * -4 relational operators: = /= != < > <= >= & (bit-AND) &=
      (masked-eq) * (present);
    * -4 logical operators: <AND>/<OR>/<NOT>/<XOR> (nestable); top-level
      tests AND. A malformed operator tail degrades gracefully, no crash.
- SSLENGTH, SSNAME, SSADD (0/1/2-arg), SSDEL, SSMEMB with duplicate-safe
  membership (re-adding a member does not grow the set; ssdel of a
  non-member returns nil).
- ENTNEXT/ENTLAST traversal as the fallback path.
- Tests assert semantic set MEMBERSHIP + data, not iteration order.

Out of scope (documented; fail CLEANLY, never crash)
----------------------------------------------------
- Interactive ssget: no-mode (interactive pick), point/window forms, and
  the graphical modes "_C" "_I" "_W" "_CP" "_WP" "_F" "L" "P" "A" —
  signal a catchable AutoLISP error (:host-not-supported /
  :unsupported-ssget-mode), recoverable by vl-catch-all-apply / *error*.
- sssetfirst/ssgetfirst grip highlighting: modelled as plain pickfirst
  storage, no graphics.
- nentsel/entsel interactive picking: nil M6 stubs.
These are inherent to a headless (model-only) engine; not defects.

Tests
-----
- clautolisp/autolisp-mock-host/tests/selection-tests.lisp (grammar:
  comma, OR/AND/NOT/XOR, relational, -3 xdata, handle, malformed tail).
- clautolisp/autolisp-mock-host/tests/dictionary-api-tests.lisp
  (ssget-x-excludes-non-graphical-objects).
- clautolisp/autolisp-builtins-core/tests/drawing-data-tests.lisp (E2E
  ssget filter grammar + membership ops + interactive-mode clean fail).
- Portable probe autolisp-front-end/tests/scenarios/entities/
  selection-probe.lsp (:clautolisp-only green now + :bricscad-only /
  :autocad-only self-skipping). Every scan is fenced to the probe's own
  entities by an XData filter, so assertions hold on a non-empty drawing.
Full `test-system "clautolisp"`: 5482 checks, Fail 0.
